The paper proposes a new algorithm for efficient Bayesian regression, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of neural networks and meta-learning suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), while the application to simulated robotic systems and a driving task suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO, cs.SY). The use of neural networks for feature encoding also suggests a potential application to computer vision (cs.CV).
